documentation is under
cd Desktop/Programming/Python/Atlas_Optimization/publishable_projects/calipy/calipy/docs/build/html/index.html

when some functions / classes not clickable: include their name in "usage", then in command line: make clean, make html



# For first run:
pip install -U "jinja2>=2.11"
pip install -U "sphinx>=5.0"
pip install --upgrade sphinxcontrib-mermaid
pip install sphinx_rtd_theme

for markdown files to be parsed also, install and enable myst-parser
pip install "myst-parser<3"

In docs/source/conf.py add the following:
"
extensions = [
   'sphinx.ext.duration',
   'sphinx.ext.doctest',
   'sphinx.ext.autodoc',
   'sphinx.ext.autosummary',
   'myst_parser',
   'sphinxcontrib.mermaid', 
]

# Parse *.rst with the ReST parser and *.md with MyST
source_suffix = {
    '.rst': 'restructuredtext',
    '.md' : 'myst',        # <- DO NOT write "myst_parser" here
}
"

